The 41st Kaduna International Trade Fair is slated to take place between 28th February to 8th March, 202o at the trade fair complex along Kaduna-Zaria road. The trade fair which is organized by the Kaduna State Chamber of Commerce, Industry, Mines and Agriculture (KADCCIMA) is expected to witness a large turnout of both local and international participants. Addressing newsmen as part of activities preparatory to the trade fair, the 2nd Deputy President and Chairman, 41st Trade Fair Organising Committee, Alhaji Suleiman Aliyu said countries such Algeria, Pakistan, Morocco, India, Germany, Egypt, Ghana, Bangladesh, Niger Republic and the Peoples Republic of China have expressed interest in participate at the fair. He said, the fair with the theme: ‘Unlocking Nigeria’s Economic Potentials Through Regional Integration’ was chosen in order to identified with the Nigerian Government as the country signed into the Africa Continental Free Trade Area (AFCTA). Aliyu said: “As part of our preparation for the fair, we have made contact with industrialists, manufacturers, producers, fabricators, distributors  and marketers both within and outside the country and have invited them to come and participate at this year’s fair. “We have also contacted policy makers, Federal Ministries of Commerce, NIPC, Trade and Investment Division of Ministry of Foreign Affairs, NACCIMA as well as the various chambers of Commerce across the country and many other stakeholders to partner in the promotion of the fair.”